<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-298-157  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 298 157.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MIS Week  Jan 23 1989 v10 n4 p11(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>System for translating languages underway. (for voices)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Inaba, Minoru.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Matsushita Electric Industrial Co Ltd has demonstrated a machinethat is able to interpret spoken Japanese and translate it intoEnglish in five seconds.andP;  The company expects to bring the machineto the market in about two years.The speech translation systemconsists of a Sun3 workstation, a voice recognition unit, and avoice synthesizing unit.andP;  The current prototype is about the sizeof a microcomputer, but a company spokesman said that in fouryears it will be the size of a pocket calculator and cost aslittle as $390.andP;  The system uses the Japanese-English translationalgorithm developed by Carnegie Mellon University.andP;  The machinehas a limited vocabulary and is designed for limited applications.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Matsushita Electric Industrial Company Ltd. (product development).andO;Topic:     Product DevelopmentVoice RecognitionVoice SynthesisLanguage TranslationJapanese Language.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>